    <note>Wei(5) Renpu [8157] A clerk (xiaoli) at the end of the Later Jin dynasty. Wang(2) Gui, in his funerary inscription for Renpu's great granddaughter (wife of Zhao(1) Shoujie [3210] [q.v.]), traces ancestry to a descendant of the ancestors of the Julu Wei(5), who settled in Rencheng (modern Jining). Xia(2) Song, in his funerary inscription for son, Xianxin [7093], also traces ancestry to Julu Wei(5), but has residence in Daming before move to Wei(d) Jixian(b). I am treating as Julu Wei(5), but not attempting to trace ancestry beyond residence in Jixian. Renpu was Zhang(1) Xun(2)'s [232] stepfather. His great granddaughter was Wang(2) Hui's [1821] (qv.) mother-in-law. Wudai jiangxiang dachen nianbiao (ESWSBB); Wang Gui, WJ, 52.7a. CBD, 5, 4245.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:954:  Apt. Shumi fushi (State Council)954:  Promoted to Shumi shi959:  Promoted to concurrent Pingzhang shi</note>
